.B
\fBreceive_response(SSH, ChannelId, End) ->\fR
\fB                          {ok, Data} | {timeout, Data} | {error, Reason}\fR
\fB                          when\fR
\fB                              SSH :: connection(),\fR
\fB                              ChannelId :: ssh_channel_id(),\fR
\fB                              End :: fun((string()) -> boolean()),\fR
\fB                              Data :: string(),\fR
\fB                              Reason :: term();\fR
\fB                      (SSH, ChannelId, Timeout) ->\fR
\fB                          {ok, Data} | {timeout, Data} | {error, Reason}\fR
\fB                          when\fR
\fB                              SSH :: connection(),\fR
\fB                              ChannelId :: ssh_channel_id(),\fR
\fB                              Timeout :: timeout(),\fR
\fB                              Data :: string(),\fR
\fB                              Reason :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Receives expected data from server on the specified session channel (see \fIreceive_response/4\fR).

.PP
Equivalent to \fIreceive_response(SSH, ChannelId, End, DefaultTimeout)\fR if called with End being function.

.PP
Equivalent to \fIreceive_response(SSH, ChannelId, close, Timeout)\fR if called with Timeout being integer.


.RE
.B
\fBreceive_response(SSH, ChannelId, End, Timeout) ->\fR
\fB                          {ok, Data} | {timeout, Data} | {error, Reason}\fR
\fB                          when\fR
\fB                              SSH :: connection(),\fR
\fB                              ChannelId :: ssh_channel_id(),\fR
\fB                              End ::\fR
\fB                                  close | timeout |\fR
\fB                                  fun((string()) -> boolean()),\fR
\fB                              Timeout :: timeout(),\fR
\fB                              Data :: string(),\fR
\fB                              Reason :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Receives expected data from server on the specified session channel.

.PP
If \fIEnd == close\fR, data is returned to the caller when the channel is closed by the server. If a time-out occurs before this happens, the function returns \fI{timeout,Data}\fR (where \fIData\fR is the data received so far).

.PP
If \fIEnd == timeout\fR, a time-out is expected and \fI{ok,Data}\fR is returned both in the case of a time-out and when the channel is closed.

.PP
If \fIEnd\fR is a fun, this fun is called with one argument, the data value in a received \fIssh_cm\fR message (see \fIssh_connection\fR. The fun is to return either \fItrue\fR to end the receiving operation (and have the so far collected data returned) or \fIfalse\fR to wait for more data from the server. Even if a fun is supplied, the function returns immediately if the server closes the channel).


